\begin_layout Standard
Overall, our results suggest that under plausible conditions there is a
 second-best rationale for contracting jointly on deforestation reductions
 and universal cash transfers.
 As we saw, there might also be a first best rationale.
 Our results suggest that if one starts with separate mechanisms contracting
 only on deforestation reduction and only on universal cash transfers, respectiv
ely, then better outcomes in both dimensions, i.e.
